title: Grateful Dead Live at The Matrix on 1966-12-01
taper: 3 great sources of this music were provided by ANON to make this version, 2 were used Almost Certainly Recorded by Peter Abrams
description:
Set I
Minglewood Blues, Betty & Dupree, Next Time You See Me, I Know You Rider, Big Boss Man, One Kind Favor, Alice D. Millionaire, Me & My Uncle, Cream Puff War
Set II
You Don't Love Me, Beat It On Down The Line, It Hurts Me Too, On The Road Again, Look Over Yonder's Wall, My Own Fault, Down So Long, Cold Rain & Snow, Viola Lee Blues
Set III
Deep Elem Blues, There's Something On Your Mind, Big Boy Pete, Death Don't Have No Mercy, Lindy, Dancin' In The Streets, Me & My Uncle
Comment
"Merry-Go-Round Broke Down" Tuning after, Me & My Uncle - Other artist(s): Jerry Pond

reviews.review_text: 12/1/66 Without The Hiss !!! I've loved this show for a long, long time but, the hiss from my old tape was always a drawback. I am very thankful to the Deadlist Project and Matt Vernon et al for working on and uploading this new source since the hiss is almost gone! The one minus from this is that the high end is absent. But, but , but... that high end loss can easily be remedied with editing software. Thanks again . Much appreciated.
